added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Justice League Edition Part 1
added.description: The Justice League holds yet another talent competition, only this time they're facing off against the Titans.

added.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Justice League Edition Part 2
added.description: In order to be the most talented superhero team in the DC universe, Robin and Beast Boy must work together on a jazz performance.

added.title: Slapping Butts and Celebrating for No Reason
added.description: When the Big Game is threatened the Titans must infiltrate the football stadium and stop the attack.
Cyborg's real strength comes not from his robot parts, but from his favorite song.

added.title: The Test
added.description: Gumball is livid when an online test keeps telling him that his character-type is "The Loser". He's convinced the only way to shake off this label is to do the opposite of everything he normally would. But Gumball suppressing his natural instincts leaves a vacuum, a Gumball-shaped hole that someone has to fill. That someone is Tobias, who starts turning the whole show into a cliched sitcom.

added.title: The Vase
added.description: Sick of Granny Jojo's ugly gifts, Nicole encourages the kids to take matters into their own hands and accidentally break her latest hideous vase. But when Gumball, Darwin and Anais try to destroy it, they discover it is more robust than it seems.

added.title: The Cycle
added.description: Gumball, Darwin and Anais discover that Mr Wilson has been picking on their Dad for most of his life; ever since he humiliated Richard with a high school prank. The kids try to work Dad through it but when their efforts fail, they realize that getting back at Mr Wilson is the only way to break the cycle.

added.title: The Grades
added.description: Miss Simian discovers a failed test from Gumball's past that brings down his grade point average. This means he has to retake kindergarten all over again, much to her delight. But by demoting him Miss Simian has inadvertently brought herself down, and they're left with no choice but to team up if they want things back to normal.

added.title: The Ex
added.description: Gumball discovers that Rob, his old nemesis, is "neme-seeing" someone else now. Devastated that Rob has fallen out of hate with him, Gumball refuses to accept that his ex-nemesis has moved on and does his best to sabotage Rob's blossoming relationship with his new foe, Banana Joe.

added.title: High Baby Fashion
added.description: The Bears enter Panda into a fashion contest, but he's got some fierce competition when Madam Malin and Madeline show up!

added.title: Teddi Bear
added.description: In an endless junkyard the Bears meet Teddi, a sentient teddy bear.

added.title: Monster in the Garden
added.description: Craig is determined to catch the monster that has been wreaking havoc in Granddad's garden.

added.title: The Curse
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP run afoul of some no-good teenage witches and are cursed! Lousy teenagers!

added.title: Dog Decider
added.description: Unable to make tough decisions, Craig decides to put his choices in the hands of a dog named Fred.

added.title: Bring Out Your Beast
added.description: Craig wants to play a popular card game, so he decides to borrow Bernard's vintage and valuable cards.

added.title: Lost in the Sewer
added.description: Craig agrees to help The Sewer Queen map the sewers, but he quickly finds himself in over his head.

added.title: Be Claws I Love You, Shelley
added.description: When Owen bring a lobster in for show and tell we discover that Chef has a real lobster problem.

added.title: Total Trauma Rama
added.description: Duncan, normally the bad kid, has an identity crisis when his pranks start curing people of their fears.

added.title: Student Becomes the Teacher
added.description: Chef is knocked unconscious right before a School Board Evaluator shows up for a big review. Now Owen has to fill in so Chef doesn't lose his Teaching License and to ensure the kids earn the pony ride Chef promised for good behavior.

added.title: Beth and the Beanstalk
added.description: After having a chocolate bar confiscated by Chef, Beth finds herself in a parallel giant world and aims to get back her now giant chocolate bar.

added.title: Pinata Regatta
added.description: Izzy can't bring herself to smash a Pinata during the class' Cinco De Mayo celebrations. But when that unsmashed Pinata comes to life and spawns an evil Pinata Army, it's batter up.

added.title: Aluxes
added.description: When Vic finds an ancient relic that summons a gang of mischievous creatures, he uses them to do his bidding, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: Go With the Flow
added.description: When Sal stays with Vic & Val, the boys are annoyed by him as their roommate but eventually they learn how cool and magical he is.

added.title: Guillermo's Gathering
added.description: When Vic & Val are forced to go to Guillermo's boring birthday party, they devise a scheme to leave early, but end up discovering that the party is way cooler than they thought.

added.title: Balloon Boys
added.description: Vic & Val go on a hot air balloon trip with Sal and compete to be his favorite, but things go awry when they try to use the magical Nazca Lines to their advantage.

added.title: Subway
added.description: The Bears are stranded on a subway platform after missing their train. But while waiting, the Bears are challenged with recovering some lost items.

added.title: Anger Management
added.description: In order to appear on a successful kids show, Nom Nom must successfully complete anger management, with Grizz as his partner.

added.title: Panda's Friend
added.description: Panda uses an app to find a friend with whom he has more common with. Soon things take a turn for the worse when the new friend gets too possessive.
The Baby Bears' dreams come true when they find a 100 dollar bill. But when they can't bear to spend it, they realize it's difficult to let go.

added.title: Neighbors
added.description: Some new neighbors set up camp next to the Bears' cave. Panda and Ice love it, but Grizz thinks they're up to no good.

added.title: Apple's Focus
added.description: Apple decides to help Onion achieve his dream of competing on a baking show.

added.title: Lil Noodle
added.description: Apple and Onion must remain legit enough to be in their favorite rapper's music video.

added.title: Gyranoid of the Future
added.description: Apple and Onion are dead set on riding Gyranoid of the Future, the craziest roller coaster at the carnival.

added.title: Fun Proof
added.description: Apple and Onion want to become this week's "Most Fun People".

added.title: Whale Spotting
added.description: In order to see a rare whale, Apple and Onion have to become members of an exclusive club, but one of them doesn't quite have the chops.

added.title: Half-Sies
added.description: During a trip to the Lake of the Ozarks, Ben and Gwen squabble over Ben's unnecessary "half-birthday" celebration, but when Max gets word of a suspicious rockslide nearby, the cousins must put aside their differences if they are to rescue the trapped miners and uncover who is behind the manmade catastrophe before it's too late: the Bugg Brothers.

added.title: Xingo's Back
added.description: Left to entertain himself as Max takes a much deserved nap, Ben stumbles upon a Xingo arcade game and goes OE-Shock Rock to power it up, but when it receives too much juice, Xingo leaps out into the real world and our hero must go toe-to-toe with his favorite cartoon character.

added.title: Bounty Ball
added.description: While Gwen listens to a lecture on the Transcontinental Railroad, Ben sneaks away to the gift shop. But once the Bounty Hunters appear and corner our hero, Gwen must relay the information she learned on the train and use it to their advantage to help Ben escape.

added.title: Fear the Fogg
added.description: As Max attempts to get Ben and Gwen to the Four Corners Monument before sunset, an ominous fog bank engulfs the roadway and forces Max to drive at a snails pace, but once The Fogg comes to life and attacks the Rust Bucket, Team Tennyson must work together if they are to navigate to safety.

added.title: The Charm Offensive
added.description: After Ben gets too much publicity for his alien antics in Fort Knox, a jealous Gwen feels unappreciated and looks to ease her pain with ice cream, but once she is confronted by Charmcaster looking to avenge Michael Morningstar, Gwen must prove to herself she's a worthy member of Team Tennyson if they are to survive.

added.title: #HappyBirthdayZee
added.description: Zatanna makes a birthday wish that forces her to confront the dark side of her magic.

added.title: #TheGreenRoom
added.description: When Jessica is faced with a Green Lantern Corps disciplinary hearing, Hal appoints himself to be her Peer Advocate.

added.title: #EnterNightSting
added.description: Karen is given a mission to prevent the apocalypse by DeathSting, a super-cool future version of herself.

added.title: #WorldsFinest
added.description: When PR whiz Max Lord tells Batgirl and Supergirl he can improve their image by doing publicity stunts, the two friends forget what being a hero is really about.

added.title: #WorkingStiff
added.description: After Babs hooks Karen up with a job at the Burrito Bucket the two heroes encounter a new villain, the scourge of the fast-food underworld, the Condiment King!

added.title: Developing Dilemna
added.description: Frankie lets Elliott get a pet, which doesn't go down well with their new neighbor.

added.title: Inadvertant Inversion
added.description: As Elliott, Mo and Frankie all try something new at the Hive, they find their worlds are about to be turned upside down again.

added.title: Stuck Together
added.description: Steven and Lars spend some time together.

added.title: The Trial
added.description: Steven goes on trial.

added.title: Off Colors
added.description: Steven finds some unusual new allies.

added.title: Lars' Head
added.description: Lars finally lets Steven in.

added.title: Dewey Wins
added.description: Steven helps Mayor Dewey run a difficult campaign.

added.title: Stuck Up, Up and Away/Schoolhouse Rocked
added.description: Stuck Up, Up and Away: Bratty little Princess comes to town and wants to be a Powerpuff Girl. When she doesn't get what she wants, the girls will have to pay./Schoolhouse Rocked: The Gangreen Gang goes back to school at Pokey Oaks Kindergarten and become the school bullies. Since the girls can't fight in school, how can they stop them?

added.title: Just Another Manic Mojo/Mime for a Change
added.description: Just Another Manic Mojo: The Powerpuff Girls lose their baseball in Mojo's house, offering him the perfect opportunity to destroy these pesky superheroines if he can only get them to sit still./Mime for a Change: An accidental bleach spill turns Rainbow the Clown into the malevolent Mr. Mime. He proceeds to turn Townsville black and white and dead all over.

added.title: Collect Her/Supper Villain
added.description: Collect Her: A fan of the Powerpuff Girls has collected every bit of Powerpuff stuff available, almost. His collection will be complete with three more items./Supper Villain: The girls' neighbor reveals he's not exactly the nice guy next door. But how will they capture him during a seemingly innocent dinner party?

added.title: Beat Your Greens/Down N' Dirty
added.description: Beat Your Greens: When Broccoli Aliens from space invade Townsville, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls and all the children of Townsville to take a bite out of crime. Down N' Dirty: When Buttercup refuses to take a bath, the town kicks her out. But Buttercup decides to stick with her stink until her favorite thing is taken away from her.

added.title: Bubblevicious/The Bare Facts
added.description: Bubblevicious: Bubbles is tired of people dismissing her as more sugar than spice. When she sets out to prove she's hardcore, she takes everyone by surprise, even Mojo Jojo./The Bare Facts: After Mojo kidnaps and blindfolds him, the Mayor has to rely on the girls' very different individual accounts of the crime to figure out exactly what happened.

added.title: Uh, Oh, Dynamo
added.description: Worried about his little girls' safety, the Professor creates Powerpuff Dynamo, a state-of-the-art protection system, to help them in battle.

added.title: The Rowdy Ruff Boys
added.description: Mojo Jojo creates the ultimate weapons against the Powerpuff Girls, boy equivalents! Enter Butch, Boomer and Brick, The Rowdyruff Boys.

added.title: Dream Scheme/You Snooze, You Lose
added.description: Dream Scheme: The Sandman would like a little rest so he puts the world to sleep. The girls must battle him in his dreams to get things back to normal./You Snooze, You Lose: When the Amoeba Boys find Mojo's plan to destroy the Powerpuff Girls, the girls unwittingly help them build a machine for their own destruction.

added.title: Birthday Bash/Too Pooped to Puff
added.description: Birthday Bash: It's the girls birthday and some special presents have arrived from the girls' main enemies. Can they destroy these evil gifts without destroying their party?/Too Pooped to Puff: The girls become exhausted when the town begins to over use them. They go on strike and end up teaching the townspeople how to fend for themselves.

added.title: Cat Man Do/Impeach Fuzz
added.description: Cat Man Do: Bubbles saves a seemingly innocent kitty from the clutches of an evil villain. But when the girls discover it's actually the Cat who is evil, they must save the Professor from being the next victim./Impeach Fuzz: When Fuzzy Lumkins throws his hat into the mayoral ring and claims a surprise victory, it's up to the Mayor and the girls to wrestle the office, and the Mayor's actual hat, back from him.

added.title: Total Eclipse of the Kart
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls compete in a race against some of their most vicious villains to win whatever is in the Mayor's mysterious box of mystery.

added.title: The Long Skate Home
added.description: After they get accused of a crime they didn't commit, the Powerpuff girls and the Derbytantes have to find a way to clear their name!

added.title: Quarantine
added.description: After a chemical spill, the girls and Mojo find themselves trapped together.

added.title: In the Doghouse
added.description: Buttercup must go it alone to save her family from a kidnapping.

added.title: Salamander
added.description: When the professor is kidnapped, the girls must go to a mysterious island to save him.

added.title: All the Little People
added.description: Magic Man secretly slips Finn a bag filled with miniature versions of Finn and all his friends.

added.title: Jake the Dad
added.description: Jake's a daddy, but being a father and keeping his rainicorn pups from killing themselves or each other is a lot harder than he imagined.

added.title: Mystery Dungeon
added.description: Ice King, NEPTR, Tree Trunks, Shelby and Lemongrab are trapped inside a mysterious dungeon and must work together to free themselves.

added.title: Little Dude
added.description: While Finn and Jake go swimming, Finn's hat magically comes to life!

added.title: The Great Bird Man
added.description: Finn and Jake get lost in the badlands and are saved by Xergiok, ex-Goblin King who now lives in cave.

added.title: Dungeon Crawl!
added.description: Having joined forces with the Lowly in their quest to defeat King Vangelis, Cole, Wu, and Vania have to find a way out of the bottom of the mountain, a place said to be inescapable.

added.title: Grief Bringer
added.description: Nya and Kai, who have become the respective leaders of the Munce and Geckles, attempt to unite the tribes in an effort to defeat their mutual enemy, the Skull Sorcerer, who schemes against them.

added.title: The Upply Strike Back!
added.description: Cole and the Upply arrive at the Skull Sorcerer's keep in the hopes of rescuing Lloyd and the other ninja. But in order to do so, Cole will need to retrieve his mother's fabled swords, the Blades of Deliverance, which are hidden somewhere inside the keep!

added.title: The Son of Lilly
added.description: The battle for the fate of Shintaro Mountain concludes!

added.title: Capture the Flag
added.description: Water balloon fights, warring factions and the risk of jail time, everything is on the line when Clarence and friends play the biggest game of capture the flag yet! Everyone wants to take home the crown, and the power to control the neighborhood's juice boxes.

added.title: Cloris
added.description: When Clarence befriends an aging woman at the local retirement home, he's determined to remind her of her old self in order to convert the grumpy granny to his fun loving ways.

added.title: Fishing Trip
added.description: Mel learns that Chad has never taken Clarence fishing, a tradition he sees as a rite of passage, and decides to remedy this with a bonding trip for all the boys! Split into two groups, Mel and Clarence learn a bit about each other while Chad struggles with the ins and outs of fishing.

added.title: Belson's Backpack
added.description: After an accidental backpack swap, Clarence discovers that Belson is hiding an artistic side and attempts to foster Belson's creativity.

added.title: Motel
added.description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

added.title: The Return of Party Horse
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to help their friend Party Horse get back together with his girlfriend.

added.title: Sleep Cycle
added.description: After staying up for two straight nights watching a movie marathon, Mordecai and Rigby have to get their sleep cycle back on track.

added.title: Just Friends
added.description: Rigby and Eileen get called away to Don's black belt ceremony forcing Mordecai and Margaret to hang out alone.

added.title: Benson's Pig
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to take Benson's new pet pig back to his apartment.

added.title: The Eileen Plan
added.description: Rigby doesn't think he's smart enough for Eileen and decides to go back and finally get his high school diploma.

added.title: Together Forever
added.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Steven visits a doctor for the first time.

added.title: Magnus P.I.
added.description: There's a been a string of thefts and each one has involved a Bakugan. The AAAnimus security force have decided the only brawler who could be responsible is: Magnus. The shock of this accusation sets Magnus off to takes justice in his own hands and go after the thief himself./Magnus foils the latest burglary attempt by the phantom thief, and in doing so, discovers the brawler partners with a golden Bakugan.  Magnus is now more interested in a brawl, than stopping any crime.

added.title: Awesome Brawlers Training  Camp
added.description: The Awesome Brawlers head to a training facility owned by Kasami International to prepare for the Bakugan Battle League - Los Volmos. But once the gang figures out they will all be competing against each other for the same title, the "team building" retreat doesn't quite go as planned./Agit turns up at the Kasami training facility and fits right in with the Awesome brawlers. This is a lifestyle that he can get used to, but it becomes apparent Agit is torn between a life as a phantom thief and life as a brawler.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League Begins/Riot vs. Ajit
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League Begins: The qualifying rounds for the Bakugan Battle league are taking place all around Los Volmos. The Awesome Brawlers all make it through into the tournament without a hitch, that is all but Dan. Dan faces an old rival in Trey, who's back with a few tricks up his sleeve./Riot vs. Ajit: The Bakugan battle league is finally here and 16 brawlers have qualified to enter including all the Awesome Brawlers. The first round will feature a brawl between China Riot and the golden Bakugan brawler, Agit!

added.title: Kung Fu Master/A Battle of Popularity
added.description: Kung Fu Master: Dan's first match-up of the Bakugan battle league is the Chinese Champion Brawler: Zhao. His opponent is a deeply focused, and serious brawler, who uses Kung Fu techniques in battle. It's going to take all Dan and Drago's focus and strength to get through this opponent!/A Battle of Popularity: Shun and Wynton's first match-ups in the Bakugan battle league take place at the same time. Even though they're not battling each other, Wynton can't help getting a little competitive with Shun, bragging that he can get the crowd cheering louder than Shun. The brawls quickly turn into a popularity contest, instead of a Bakugan battle!

added.title: The Mysterious Revenger/Wynton vs. Lia
added.description: The Mysterious Revenger: It's the quarter finals of the Bakugan Battle League, the top eight brawlers are set to face off! In this round, Dan will face off against the Bakugan rocker - Revenger! These two brawlers give it their all in this icy cold clash!/Wynton Vs. Lia: The quarter finals continue, and it's the first Awesome Brawler vs. Awesome Brawler matches of the Bakugan Battle League tournament. In this round, it's Wynton vs. Lia and Shun vs. Lightning.

added.title: Dawn of the Donut
added.description: Dr. Fox's plans to deliver donuts all over the Unikingdom are sidetracked by Unikitty's reluctance to follow instructions.

added.title: P.L.O.T. Device 2: Beyond the Bored Dome
added.description: Dr. Fox reprograms the P.L.O.T. Device to only generate boring events, but the gang can't help but add drama and excitement to every scenario.

added.title: The New Nemesis
added.description: When Hawkodile discovers his old enemy Eagleator has a new nemesis in his life, the gang do all they can to get Hawk back on his foe's radar.

added.title: Baby Caterpillar
added.description: Unikitty takes in a radioactive caterpillar and raises it like a baby, unaware of the havoc it will wreak as a full-grown adult.

added.title: Borrowed
added.description: Richard discovers his library books have been borrowed by Master Frown and sets off on a crazed mission to return the books before they're overdue.

added.title: Deep Space Vacation
added.description: When Gar lets KO and Enid take a vacation to outer  space, they get more than they bargained for.

added.title: Big Reveal
added.description: KO finds out who his father is.

added.title: Radical Rescue
added.description: Rad is forced to reconsider his identity when KO starts taking on some of his traits.

added.title: You're a Good Friend, KO
added.description: KO brings Dendy along for a hero mission in order to cheer her up.

added.title: Let's Get Shadowy
added.description: KO teams up with an unlikely ally to take on an old foe.

added.title: Bobo Chan
added.description: Badgerclops adopts an abandoned monster, but some things are better left in the wild.

added.title: Small
added.description: Mao Mao's legendary, gigantic and critical father visits his son at his new job as sheriff.

added.title: Legend of Torbaclaun
added.description: When the Sweetypies think the mythical Torbaclaun has come to Pure Heart Valley, Mao Mao tries to prove to them that it isn't real.

added.title: Meet Tanya Keys
added.description: When bounty hunter Tanya Keys comes to town for Badgerclops, it's up to Mao Mao and Adorabat to save their friend -- even if he's been on the wrong side of the law.

added.title: Weapon of Choice
added.description: Worried that his sword is a glorified consolation prize, Mao Mao sets out to prove the worth of his weapon.

added.title: Lucky Girl
added.description: Ben battles an evil sorcerer whose power whose emanates from mystic charms, one of which turns Gwen into her own superhero named Lucky Girl.

added.title: A Small Problem
added.description: When Ben is not allowed on an attraction at a water park because he's too short, he decides to go alien to get even with the ride's attendant.

added.title: Side Effects
added.description: Ben catches a cold and the symptoms wreak havoc on his alien heroes. To make matters even worse, he has to battle a creature made from cockroaches.

added.title: Breakpoint
added.description: As Wildvine, Ben goes undercover with an alien crime ring and is tempted by their extreme lifestyle.

added.title: The Color of Monkey
added.description: Everybody's favorite alien conman, Argit, takes on a shady sidekick, Simian, in a shocking new business.

added.title: Vreedlemania
added.description: Pa Vreedle reunites with Ma for all-out destruction.

added.title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad Ben World Part 1
added.description: Alternate dimensions, duplicate Bens and villains from throughout time and space! Just another day in Bellwood.

added.title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad Ben World Part 2
added.description: Ben and Dr. Psychobos become reluctant allies in a parallel-dimension maelstrom.

added.title: Collection Infection
added.description: Having pared down their Magisword collection, the Warriors are forced into unconventional battle choices on a dangerous mission into the Deepest Darkest Woods.

added.title: To Balderly Go
added.description: Prohyas is crushed when his good hair day becomes a no hair day and Vambre has to battle a furry monster alone while her bro is in shock without his locks!

added.title: For the Love of Narwhal
added.description: Vambre rejects Darlin' Narwhal Magisword as being unfit for battle, but when Prohyas trains and brings out its full potential, Vambre resorts to improper extremes to get it back.

added.title: Winning at Whining
added.description: Vambre's challenge to Prohyas: Don't whine for the entirety of the next mission and you can have the Magisword we get at the end.

added.title: Suitable Armor
added.description: A veteran warrior insists that Vambre is under dressed for battle and takes it upon herself to garb Vambre in armor as Prohyas fights the beast solo without armor.

added.title: Changeable Terraingable
added.description: Personality conflicts between Vambre and Prohyas come to a head as the Warriors miraculously manage to ace a mission at an ever changing labyrinth.

added.title: Fixing a Flonk
added.description: Wanting to stop Flonk from being an evildoer for good, Prohyas tries to find Flonk a permanent venue for his nasty comedy. Vambre, however, wants to deliver him to the cops as usual.

added.title: What's My Name? Starring Vambre and Prohyas Warrior!
added.description: The Warriors go to extreme measures so folks remember their names.

added.title: Ain't That a Kick in the Side?
added.description: After Witch Way teases Prohyas by calling him, "Vambre's sidekick," Prohyas intensifies his efforts to prove them wrong.

added.title: Vambre's Guilty Pleasure
added.description: Vambre tries her best to keep her tough Warrior reputation intact and still go to the cutesy wootsy Piggiepie Jones stage show.

added.title: Doctor Visit
added.description: Uncle Grandpa hates going to the doctor but he's overdue for an important vaccination.

added.title: The Cake Mistake
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus eat a cake meant for someone else.

added.title: Sheep Deprivation
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a kid who can't fall asleep.

added.title: Trash Cat
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a cat who's afraid to take baths.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa's Odd-yssey
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang must retrieve Tiger from the pound before she's adopted out.

added.title: Sigue la corriente
added.description: Cuando Sal se queda en lo de Vic y Val, los chicos no lo soportan como compañero, pero finalmente descubren lo genial y mágico que es.

added.title: Aluxes
added.description: Vic encuentra una antigua reliquia que invoca a una pandilla de traviesas criaturas, iy las consecuencias son desastrosas!

added.title: La Fiesta de Guillermo
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val se ven forzados a ir a la aburrida fiesta de cumpleaños de Guillermo, crean un plan para irse temprano, pero terminan descubriendo que la fiesta es mucho mejor de lo que pensaban.

added.title: Ninos de Globo
added.description: Vic y Val salen de viaje en globo aerostático con Sal y compiten por ser su favorito, pero las cosas se complican cuando tratan de usar las mágicas líneas de Nazca a su favor.

added.title: El Gran Robo de Bongos
added.description: Los chicos olvidan conseguir un regalo para Chata en el Día de la Abuela y en un movimiento desesperado, le regalan los bongos que pidieron prestados a Xochi. Sabiendo que deben devolver los tambores, Victor y Valentino fingen ser ladrones para robar los instrumentos.

added.title: Atrapados juntos
added.description: Steven y Lars pasan algo de tiempo juntos.

added.title: La prueba
added.description: Steven va a juicio.

added.title: Descoloridas
added.description: Steven encuentra unos nuevos aliados fuera de lo común.

added.title: La cabeza de Lars
added.description: Lars por fin deja pasar a Steven.

added.title: Dewey gana
added.description: Steven ayuda al alcalde Dewey a llevar adelante una campaña difícil.

added.title: Golpeando Traseros Y Celebrando Sin Razon
added.description: Cuando el Gran Partido es amenazado, los Titanes deben infiltrarse en el estadio de futbol americano para detener el ataque.

added.title: El Estudiante se Hace Maestro
added.description: Chef queda insconsciente justo antes de que una evaluadora de la junta escolar aparezca para una inspección. Ahora Owen tiene que reemplazarlo para que Chef no pierda su licencia de maestro y para asegurar que los chicos ganen el paseo en pony que Chef les prometió por su buena conducta.

added.title: Beth y la Planta de Frijoles
added.description: Después de que Chef les confiscara una barra de chocolate, Beth se encuentra en un mundo paralelo gigante y quiere recuperar su barra que ahora es enorme.

added.title: El Dia de la Pinata
added.description: Izzy no logra golpear una piñata durante las celebraciones del Cinco de Mayo de la clase. Pero cuando esa piñata sin aplastar cobra vida y genera un ejército de piñatas malignas, es la hora de la verdad.

added.title: A Media
added.description: Durante un viaje al Lago de los Ozarks, Ben y Gwen discuten sobre la innecesaria celebración de "medio cumpleaños" de Ben. Pero cuando Max se entera de un sospechoso desprendimiento de rocas cercano, los primos deben dejar de lado sus diferencias si quieren rescatar a los mineros atrapados y revelar quién está detrás de la catástrofe producida por el hombre antes de que sea demasiado tarde: los hermanos Bugg.

added.title: El regreso de Xingo
